  "description": [
    "ImmigrationLeading Topic of Measures in Congress Now 51 Bills Proposing Various Amendments Most of These Sponsored by House Members Immigration more than any other subject has drawn the attention of lawmakers during the opening days of the 70th Congress Already 51 bills have been intro duced proposing various amend ments to existing immigration laws Most of these are sponsored by House members Would Deport Aliens Chairman Albert Johnson of the House Immigration Committee rein troduced his bill for deportation of aliens It is indorsed by the Bureau of Immigration and the Secretary of Labor and is designed to give the bureau greater power in deporta tion cases A number of other de portation bills differing in minor features are also before Congress A measure requiring registration of all aliens in this country some what similar to registration laws In effect in European countries has also been reintroduced It too is indorsed by the Immigration Bureau but is strongly opposed by liberal members of Congress Rep Blanton Tex proposes to suspend all immigration to this country until 1935 but would per mit emergency farm laborers to enter temporarily from Mexico and Canada Copeland Leads Fight The fight for repeal of the"
